# skhd in the AeroSpace era: hold-to-repeat resize keys ONLY.
# AeroSpace fires a binding once per physical press (its hotkey API gets no key
# autorepeat), while skhd fires on every autorepeat keydown — so the resize
# chords live here and repeat while held.
#
# Passthrough: skhd consumes cmd-alt-b, so IT owns the toggle while running.
# Entering a mode runs the command after the ':', which syncs AeroSpace and
# sketchybar. In passthrough mode the resize chords are unbound and reach apps.
# If skhd is stopped, the same chords fall through to aerospace.toml, where
# identical fallback bindings (single-step resize, own passthrough mode) live.
#
# Old yabai-era config kept next to this file: skhdrc.yabai

:: default : /opt/homebrew/bin/aerospace mode main; /opt/homebrew/bin/sketchybar --trigger aerospace_mode_change MODE=main
:: passthrough : /opt/homebrew/bin/aerospace mode passthrough; /opt/homebrew/bin/sketchybar --trigger aerospace_mode_change MODE=passthrough

cmd + alt - b ; passthrough
passthrough < cmd + shift + alt - b ; default
# Also bound in default mode (as in the yabai-era config): keeps the chord from
# leaking to apps, and re-entering default re-runs the sync command above, so
# it doubles as a "force back to main" if the two ever disagree.
cmd + shift + alt - b ; default

# y/o move the vertical divider left/right, u/i the horizontal one down/up.
shift + alt - y : ~/.config/aerospace/scripts/divider-resize.sh left 20
shift + alt - o : ~/.config/aerospace/scripts/divider-resize.sh right 20
shift + alt - u : ~/.config/aerospace/scripts/divider-resize.sh down 20
shift + alt - i : ~/.config/aerospace/scripts/divider-resize.sh up 20

ctrl - f8 : ~/.config/aerospace/scripts/divider-resize.sh left 40
ctrl - f10 : ~/.config/aerospace/scripts/divider-resize.sh right 40
shift - f8 : ~/.config/aerospace/scripts/divider-resize.sh up 20
shift - f10 : ~/.config/aerospace/scripts/divider-resize.sh down 20
